  "description": "Giovanni's is a little Italian pizza place run by a chef who uses his own recipes, and serves fresh from a clay oven. ",
  "reviews": "If you love pizza, you definitely should know Giovanni's. By pizza, I mean the authentic kind, not the stuffy bread-type kind. Anyway, they have been our go-to spot for some delicious pizza for as long as we can remember. And now, they have pasta too!\nIt's located on right opposite Moon River Chinese restaurant on Thimbirigasyaya Road.\nTheir menu has changed since our last visit with a few new meat additions and of course, the pasta. They have a separate menu for that so make sure you specifically ask for it, otherwise, they would just hand you the pizza menu.\nThe Spaghetti Bolognese\u00a0(Rs. 1400) we got was superb! Just like with their pizza, they have not skimped on the meat. While it was cooked perfectly with the right amount of spiciness, and seasoning, there was enough minced beef bolognese to feed at least two hungry mouths. The spaghetti itself was homecooked and it was much better than the\u00a0Spaghetti Bolognese we had at\nfor the same price. It was a delicious, hefty portion which was well worth the price.\nThey also have other options like Carbonara\u00a0and a few different varieties\u00a0of Risotto.\nIt would be sacrilege\u00a0to go to Giovanni's and not get a pizza. We got one-half\u00a0Sandeep (Rs. 1650), one of\u00a0their newest additions to the menu and the other half of\u00a0good old Margarita (Rs. 1000).\nSandeep was essentially a sausage pizza with lots of\u00a0sausage pieces, cheese and veggies like onions, bell pepper, black\u00a0olives on top. It was spicy, delicious and very cheesy.\nThe Margarita is still the best I have had and safe to say\u00a0that their\u00a0standards have not wavered at all. A margarita is as good as its simplicity\u00a0and strong flavours, and this one delivered both. The tomato sauce was thick and mildly spicy with melted mozzarella on top,\u00a0while\u00a0the fresh basil gave it a really nice kick. The red, white and green really do remind you of the Italian flag, which was not a coincidence.\nTheir service is casual, friendly and efficient as always, especially considering that the place only seems to get more crowded by the hour.\nThe ambience is pretty much the beautifully bricked wall upstairs with wooden furniture and checkered\u00a0tablecloths. They also have a more spacious area downstairs if you're bored to climb those tiny stairs.\nGiovanni's is as good as we remembered, if not better. Definitely check out the pasta range, it's a nice addition and one that I hope that they'll keep up the good quality and standards.\nThe best pizza place in town now has a delicious pasta range too.\nSince they first opened their doors a year ago, Giovanni\u2019s has been our go-to spot for wood-fired pizzas. This time around, even in Dimuthu\u2019s absence on the day, they still dished out the quality that we've come to expect.\nGiovanni's is a little Italian pizza place run by a chef who uses his own recipes, and serves fresh from a clay oven.\n\n\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd9 \u0d91\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dbb \u0dbb\u0dc3 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbb\u0dca \u0db6\u0ddd\u0dad\u0dbd\u0dca 3 \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0da2\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0db7\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d89\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0d9a\u0ddc.  \u0d91\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd9 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dc0. \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d94\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1.  \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0daf \u0d85\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dda\u2026 \u0db8\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf.\n\n\u0da2\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u